<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧊 M003 Week 2 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Lines &amp; Rectangles on the Wall (x, y) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week you use a <strong>loop</strong> to draw a whole <strong>line</strong> of blocks. Grow <strong>x</strong> to go across, or <strong>y</strong> to go up.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the steps. Circle your answer.</p>
<pre><code>set x to 0
repeat 4 times:
    place stone block at (x, 0)
    add 1 to x
</code></pre>
<p><strong>x grows, y stays 0. A line across, or up? Circle one:</strong> across · up</p>
<p><strong>Why? Circle one:</strong> x is the across number · y is the across number</p>
<pre><code>set y to 0
repeat 4 times:
    place stone block at (0, y)
    add 1 to y
</code></pre>
<p><strong>This time y grows, x stays 0. Across or up? Circle one:</strong> across · up</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows clean code, then a buggy version. Circle the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The line should go <strong>across</strong> the bottom of the wall.</p>
<pre><code># clean
set x to 0
repeat 4 times:
    place block at (x, 0)
    add 1 to x
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
set x to 0
repeat 4 times:
    place block at (0, x)
    add 1 to x
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which way does the buggy line go? Circle one:</strong> up · across</p>
<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The line should be <strong>4 blocks long</strong>.</p>
<pre><code># clean
set x to 0
repeat 4 times:
    place block at (x, 0)
    add 1 to x
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
set x to 0
repeat 2 times:
    place block at (x, 0)
    add 1 to x
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How long is the buggy line? Circle one:</strong> 2 blocks · 4 blocks</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>You want a line going <strong>straight up</strong> the left edge. x must stay <strong>0</strong> while y grows.</p>
<pre><code>set y to 0
repeat 4 times:
    place block at (____, y)
    add 1 to y
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which number is missing? Circle one:</strong> 0 · y · 4</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Switch to your homework world. Use a loop to draw <strong>one line going across</strong> and another for <strong>one line going up</strong>, so they meet at the corner (0, 0) and make an <strong>L</strong> shape.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
